# distributed-deque — agent memory

Read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root for the full, maintained summary.

**Topic rules:** `go-conventions.mdc` (Go files), `memory-patterns.mdc` (`memory/`, `remote/`, `cmd/`, tests). **Learning doc:** `docs/deque-guide.md`.

## What this is

Go library: **deque** with **in-memory doubly-linked list** first (`MemoryDeque`: nodes + `head`/`tail` + mutex, O(1) both ends). **Distributed** = optional **`RemoteDeque`** client to a queue server that owns the only `MemoryDeque`. Redis is **not** v1 scope. See `README.md`.

- **Module:** `github.com/williamntlam/distributed-deque`
- **Package name:** `distributeddeque`

## Implementation status

| Area | Status |
|------|--------|
| `README.md` | Design doc (in-memory first, remote optional) |
